Heavy rain and snowfall had been forecast for the weekend, as a cold front sweeps through the province. JOHANNESBURG - Rain leading to localised flooding has been forecast for parts of the Western Cape on Sunday, according to the South African Weather Services (SAWS). Heavy rain and snowfall had been forecast for the weekend, as a cold front sweeps through the province. SAWS has posted a warning of extreme weather continuing into Sunday.  SAWS has urged the public to stay safe.